      "raw_text": "1t is likely that e. A. Cooney\nwill refuse to act as local organ\nizer for the American Federation\nof Labor after March I, when his\ntenure of Office expires. With his\nelevation to the second vice presi.\ndency of the state federation he\nwill be compelled to exert himself\nin the interests of the federation\nin this city and vicinity and will\nhave no time to devote to the work\nof the A. F. of l.. There is NC\ndearth of organizers here, the A\nF. of l.. having two beside\nCooney."
